Class KeyValue

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Codec>, Codec

    public class KeyValue
extends Struct

    KeyValue structure. Since most of the keys and resultant values in Subtrate is hashed and/or encoded, this does not wrap Text, but rather a Bytes for the keys and values. (Not to be confused with the KeyValue in Metadata, that is actually for Maps, whereas this is a representation of actaul storage values)
